# Go Standards

## Config

- YAML config file primary; env for Docker override. See [docs/prd/decision-log.md](docs/prd/decision-log.md) §2 (Config, Template sources).
- Path: fixed first (e.g. /etc/kui/config.yaml), then `--config` flag or `KUI_CONFIG` env
- Load via `internal/config`; fail fast if required values missing

## Database

- Use SQLite (single file, 1–2 users)
- Use `database/sql` with `modernc.org/sqlite` or similar driver
- DB path from config YAML; env override for Docker (e.g. `KUI_DB_PATH`)

## HTTP

- Use chi router (`github.com/go-chi/chi/v5`)
- Keep routes minimal; no magic middleware

## CLI

- Use stdlib `flag` for flags
- Parse after defining; fail fast if required flags missing

## Error Handling

- Return errors; do not swallow them
- Use `slog` (log/slog) for structured logging
- Log at boundaries (main, HTTP handlers); avoid logging deep in helpers
- Use `slog.Error` + `os.Exit(1)` for startup failures

## Libvirt Testing

- Use libvirt test driver (`test:///default`) for unit tests — no mocks
- CI runs without KVM; test driver provides in-memory fake hypervisor

## Structure

- Keep `main.go` focused; extract logic to packages or helpers when it grows
- Avoid god packages; one concern per package

## Greenfield

No backwards compatibility or migration code. Implement the target design directly.
